response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Multiples\", \"description\": \"Write a function `sum_of_multiples` that finds the sum of all unique multiples of 3 or 5 below a given number `n`. Your function should take an integer `n` as input and return the sum of all unique multiples of 3 or 5 less than `n`.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_multiples(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): An integer greater than 0.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns an integer that is the sum of all unique multiples of 3 or 5 less than `n`.\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_multiples(n: int) -> int:\\n    return sum({i for i in range(1, n) if i % 3 == 0 or i % 5 == 0})\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_multiples(10) == 23\", \"assert sum_of_multiples(20) == 78\", \"assert sum_of_multiples(30) == 195\"] }"
